<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 10:39PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHEASTERN FRANKLIN...NORTHERN
TITUS AND SOUTHERN RED RIVER COUNTIES THROUGH 1115 PM CDT...
At 1039 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bogata, or 7 miles southwest of Clarksville, moving southeast at 30
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clarksville, Boxelder, Bogata, Wilkerson, Winfield, Talco, Miller`s
Cove, Harts Bluff, Johntown, and Cuthand.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
